programme.title: Panorama
programme.desc: The nation's children are going to bed later and sleeping less, which is playing havoc with their health and education - causing obesity, problems for parents and teachers and even family breakdowns. In this film, Jenny Kleeman finds that from toddlers to teenagers, youngsters' rocketing use of technology coupled with laxer modern parenting is creating an epidemic of poor sleeping habits, with more and more of children reliant on prescription drugs.(n)
